column1: Table LA1: Key stage 1 eligibility and performance of children who have been looked after continuously for at least twelve months1

column4: Number eligible for key stage 1 assessments3

column1: 1. Children looked after continuously for at least twelve months as at 31 March excluding those children in respite care. Only children who have been matched to key stage 1 data are included. This is the provisional version of key stage 1 data.

2. Includes all schools with pupils eligible for assessment at key stage 1. Participation by independent schools is voluntary, therefore only includes results from those independent schools which chose to make a return and which met the statutory standards for assessment and moderation.

3. This is the number of children eligible for key stage 1 assessments. Includes pupils who are absent, disapplied, working below/towards the expected standard and reached a higher standard at the end of key stage 1. Excludes pupils with missing teacher assessments.
4.  Includes those working at the expected standard or above.

5. The 2016 key stage 1 assessments are the first which assess the new, more challenging national curriculum, which was introduced in 2014. See link below for changes to national curriculum assessments at key stage 1:
Numbers relating to national or regional totals have been rounded to the nearest 10. Local authority numbers have been rounded to the nearest 5.
x = number less than or equal to 5 or percentage where the numerator is less than or equal to 5 or the denominator is less than or equal to 10.
See methodology and quality document for more information on rounding conventions.
